# `.envrc` example (direnv)

Copy the following into **repo root** as `.envrc`, fill in values, then run:

```bash
direnv allow
```

Then you can run `flutter run` without typing `--dart-define` flags manually.

```sh
# Local direnv config (copy to repo root as `.envrc`)
# `.envrc` is gitignored; never commit real secrets.

# Used by the FastAPI demo (if you deploy it) to call Hugging Face Inference.
# This is a secret; keep it out of git.
# export HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY="hf_..."

# Optional: AI Decision Workbench backend base URL.
# Default without this variable on all platforms:
# https://ai-decision-api.fastapicloud.dev
#
# Pick ONE only when you need to override the default:
#
# Local:
# export AI_DECISION_API_BASE_URL="http://127.0.0.1:8008"
#
# FastAPI Cloud:
# export AI_DECISION_API_BASE_URL="https://ai-decision-api.fastapicloud.dev"

# Optional: if you want Supabase to initialize from local injection.
# Note: when validating the Firebase Remote Config Supabase flow, keep these
# unset so you can prove the app is sourcing config from Remote Config.
# export SUPABASE_URL="https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co"
# export SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY"

# Optional: Firebase local development config.
# Committed `lib/firebase_options.dart` stays a placeholder; put real values here.
# After `flutterfire configure`: copy keys from generated Dart/platform files, then
# `git checkout HEAD -- lib/firebase_options.dart` (see docs/firebase_setup.md step 3b).
# `tool/flutter_dart_defines_from_env.sh` forwards these into Dart via --dart-define.
# export FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID="your-project-id"
# export FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID="000000000000"
# export FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL="https://your-project-id-default-rtdb.region.firebasedatabase.app"
# export FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET="your-project-id.appspot.com"
# export FIREBASE_ANDROID_API_KEY="YOUR_ANDROID_API_KEY"
# export FIREBASE_ANDROID_APP_ID="1:000000000000:android:placeholder"
# export FIREBASE_IOS_API_KEY="YOUR_IOS_API_KEY"
# export FIREBASE_IOS_APP_ID="1:000000000000:ios:placeholder"
# export FIREBASE_IOS_CLIENT_ID="000000000000-example.apps.googleusercontent.com"
# export FIREBASE_IOS_BUNDLE_ID="com.example.flutterBlocApp"
# export FIREBASE_MACOS_API_KEY="YOUR_MACOS_API_KEY"
# export FIREBASE_MACOS_APP_ID="1:000000000000:ios:placeholder"
# export FIREBASE_MACOS_CLIENT_ID="000000000000-example.apps.googleusercontent.com"
# export FIREBASE_MACOS_BUNDLE_ID="com.example.flutterBlocApp"

# Optional
# export GEMINI_API_KEY="..."
# export GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY="..."
# export GOOGLE_MAPS_ANDROID_API_KEY="..."

# Optional: FastAPI Cloud chat demo (preferred) (see docs/integrations/render_fastapi_chat_demo.md).
# `tool/flutter_dart_defines_from_env.sh` maps these to --dart-define for the direnv flutter wrapper.
# export CHAT_FASTAPICLOUD_DEMO_ENABLED="true"
# export CHAT_FASTAPICLOUD_DEMO_BASE_URL="https://render-chat-api.fastapicloud.dev"
# export CHAT_FASTAPICLOUD_DEMO_STRICT="false"
# export CHAT_FASTAPICLOUD_DEMO_SECRET="..."  # only if the FastAPI service gates requests
# export CHAT_FASTAPICLOUD_HF_READ_TOKEN_CALLABLE="issueRenderChatDemoHfReadToken"
# export CHAT_FASTAPICLOUD_HF_READ_TOKEN_CALLABLE_REGION="us-central1"  # omit to use default
#
# Legacy Render naming (still supported):
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_ENABLED="true"
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_BASE_URL="https://your-service.onrender.com"
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_STRICT="false"
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_SECRET="..."  # only if the FastAPI service uses DEMO_SHARED_SECRET
# export CHAT_RENDER_HF_READ_TOKEN_CALLABLE="issueRenderChatDemoHfReadToken"
# export CHAT_RENDER_HF_READ_TOKEN_CALLABLE_REGION="us-central1"  # omit to use default

# Optional: Firebase Functions emulator — Callable `issueRenderChatDemoHfReadToken` reads this
# when FUNCTIONS_EMULATOR=true (not a Flutter dart-define; export for the shell that runs `firebase emulators:start`).
# export RENDER_CHAT_DEMO_HF_READ_TOKEN="hf_..."

# Optional: Render workspace API key (local shell + Cursor MCP `Authorization: Bearer ${RENDER_API_KEY}`).
# Do NOT put this in Firebase Remote Config — the Flutter app fetches RC to the device; Render keys are admin-scoped.
# export RENDER_API_KEY="rnd_..."
# With RENDER_API_KEY set, you can trigger a service rebuild from repo root:
#   ./tool/trigger_render_chat_api_deploy.sh
# (see docs/integrations/render_fastapi_chat_demo.md — MCP cannot start deploys).

# Optional: make `flutter run` auto-append --dart-define from env (zsh/bash).
# The wrapper injects defines after the subcommand (e.g. `flutter run --dart-define=...`).
export PATH="$(pwd)/tool/direnv/bin:${PATH}"
```
